The company says it's carried the burden of rising fuel costs which have increased by 30% over the past year and is projected to increase by a further 6%. CAPE TOWN - The Golden Arrow Bus commuters will soon be paying more for their tickets. The company says it's carried the burden of rising fuel costs which have increased by 30% over the past year and is projected to increase by a further 6%. Spokesperson Bronwen Dyke-Beyer says it can no longer absorb these cost escalations. “Golden Arrow remains acutely aware of the effect of the increased fares on its passengers. And would like to assure them once again that this increase is unavoidable given the prevailing economic climate.” (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)